B.RR=new A.dg("Removed pet illnesses and detailed health information from onboarding entirely","These fields appeared early but added significant perceived effort without an obvious first-session payoff. Users were not yet invested enough in the product to feel this was a fair exchange.","A major resistance point was eliminated. Health information was moved to an in-app prompt later in the journey, where users had more context and motivation to provide it.",B.bE)
B.RO=new A.dg("Led with a feature carousel before the first form screen","Competitive analysis and usability sessions both pointed to the same gap: users had no idea what Perro would do for them before they were asked to give information. The carousel was designed to close that gap in three or four screens.","Tested against a minimal version without the carousel. The carousel variant performed better on engagement and downstream completion, and became the production baseline.",B.bE)
B.RC=new A.dg("Replaced mandatory photo upload with an avatar system and optional image","Usability sessions showed this was a silent exit trigger. Users left the app to find a suitable photo and frequently did not return. Making it optional removed a low-value blocker.","Drop-off at the dog profile step fell noticeably post-launch. Users could complete setup in a single session without leaving the app.",B.bE)
B.RL=new A.dg("Added a dedicated permissions explainer screen before OS prompts","Abrupt system dialogs for location and notifications appeared out of nowhere with no context. Most users either dismissed them or felt ambushed. A brief plain-language screen before each prompt changed the framing entirely.","Permission acceptance improved. Users who read the explainer were significantly more likely to grant both location and notification access.",B.bE)
B.RM=new A.dg("Redesigned subscription UI to echo the feature carousel benefits","The paywall previously felt disconnected from the onboarding story. By repeating the same four benefit areas from the carousel, the subscription step became a natural continuation rather than an interruption.","Subscription conversion increased and the share of users choosing longer-term plans rose. Qualitative feedback described the step as feeling \u201cfairer\u201d and \u201cmore honest\u201d.",B.bE)
B.RF=new A.dg("Moved activity level and certain fitness questions to post-signup in-app prompts","These questions were arriving when users were already fatigued and before they had done anything in the app that would make the questions feel relevant.","Reduced late-funnel fatigue. The information was still collected, just at a point in the journey where users had more reason to care about it.",B.bE)
